Deputy President William Ruto has defended the government decision to float a 202 billion shilling sovereign bond saying the monies will be used to fund development projects and will not be lost in scandals. Ruto spoke as NASA leader Raila Odinga questioned the government’s increasing appetite for loans saying the Jubilee administration was taking the country to the dogs. The International Monetary Fund- IMF had Thursday expressed concern over Kenya’s increasing debt saying it was heading to unsustainable levels. 